@DATABASE "Chronos"
@NODE "MAIN" "SPECCY POKES - C - Chronos"
@TOC "MAIN"

                   ZX SPECTRUM (SPECCY heheh) POKES - C
                   ====================================

                                  Chronos
                                  =======


DESCRIPTION              POKE
===========              ====

@{"Infinite Lives" RXS "ADDRESS COMMAND ZXAMPoke(56906,167)"}          56906,167
@{"Autofire      " RXS "ADDRESS COMMAND ZXAMPoke(26987,201)"}          26987,201
@{"Lives = x     " RXS "ADDRESS COMMAND ZXAMPoke(53407,255)"}          53407,x (x= 1-255)

                         Change x to whatever value you wish, using
                         the POKE option on the ZXAM GUI. Simply
                         click the button to get the maximum value
                         x can be (usually 255).

                         I can't test this one, as the game crashes
                         on the emulator :(

                         Rastan.
@endnode
